HEADWORD: Multiaxial
<hw>Mul`ti*ax"i*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Multi-</ets> + <ets>axial</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Having more than one axis; developing in more than a single line or
plain; -- opposed to <ant>monoaxial</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Multicapsular</ent>⟦br⟧
